column3: Tryndamere! I am the cause of your suffering! See if you can cut me from this body!"

voice_line: A bird? You would challenge me with a bird?! *Laughs* "Come!"
A lightning squirrel? *Laughs* "Thank you! Your death will amuse me!"
A scythe? A scythe?! Are you planning on murdering fields of wheat?!
A spirit blade, master Shen? Test it against me, let me shatter your illusions!
A spirit for cowards, I laugh at your tricks and mushrooms!
A statue? Rock shatters as easily as bone! Come!
A troll king?! Come! Defend your throne, king of trolls!
Ah, mastery, well done! Now master your insignificance.
All that lives, I will end!
Am I challenged by a tree?! Fine, let me build a pyre from you!
Am I the abyss? Or did I gaze into it?
Another foolish god, even the phoenix shall end.
Are you a joke, you loud, horrible thing? I shall kill you and your whistling bird too!
As long as life exists, as long as time has meaning, I am not done!
As long as this form lives, I will punish them.
Aspect of change! Now you die!
Bow worms! Bow before the World-Ender!
Carnage, hate, yes! I am the World-Ender!
Challenge me, mortals! I am here!
Cleave through them, Aatrox! Crush their skulls! Shatter their ribs! Disembowel their very souls! *Heavy breathing* "Our vengeance is at hand!"
Come closer! I will show you… darkness!
Come, let me show you darkness!
Cowardly spirit, how annoying you are! I will savor killing you, Teemo!
Dark deeds I will do this day… Though I will carry myself as my former pride dictates!
Death to all! The World-Ender awaits!
Did you think you could kill me?!
Die, Kayle, knowing your potential will never be reached.
Die, Shen, knowing the Eye of the Twilight is blinded and plucked.
Do I resemble you, abomination? Your form isn't my destiny… is it? You don't know how to talk, do you?
Do you see my edge?! Your death awaits!
Every dream is a candle I must snuff out… I… am the darkness…
For my imprisonment, they will suffer!
From entire villages and towns, I will rend the flesh… Until I stand… as an unholy god.
Gods and mortals, they deserve only death!
Guns and oranges? Are you a cliché or a joke? Come! Fight! Die!
Hail father Ornn, god of fire and forge! *Laughs* "I am Aatrox
Hail Pantheon! How noble and proud he carries himself! Come betrayer! Come brothers! Come sinners! See how the gods bleed!
Hail Pantheon! How many times must I kill you? Let the gods tremble at my feet!
Hail Pantheon! Let me hear you cry of friendship! Let me hear you scream of brotherhood!
Hail Pantheon! See the weapon I have become! Watch as you are destroyed!
Hail the protector! Hail Taric, aspect of- get a haircut!
Hear me, tree spirit. Your form is but kindling, and your forests I will burn!
Honestly, a bow and two boys? What was your plan, Varus?
How far I have fallen! A god… reduced to a prisoner!
How I loathe your freedom, trickster! I will take this vengeance upon you, until the end of times!
I am Aatrox, I am the World-Ender!
I am forgotten… until I slay the dragon once more!
I am oblivion! I am destruction! I am doom!
I am the god of death!
I dared kill gods… what more can they do to me?
I feel my flesh rotting, spoiling… soon there will be nothing left of me!
I know an executioner when I see one, Draven.
I know blood when I smell it.
I know who you truly are, mortal. I will drown you in a pool of your own blood.
I will drink from your skull!
I will drown them in oceans of blood!
I will find my love, and then I will kill you all!
I will render these mortal forms unto ash!
I will savor carving your name into my flesh, Riven. A thousand times, until you beg me to rip you apart!
I will snuff out the light from your eyes!
I will teach you to die, Tryndamere.
I will tell you a secret, Tryndamere. I was there when Aatrox slew your kin… what magic, what beauty, I know your rage. Come, let me feel your rage!
If they kill me, what better time for my return than now?!
It is such immeasurable suffering. I do not know what I am.
It matters not! I will kill them all!
Kill me, Varus! You kill us both! Then I will find you, Darkin, and I will force you inside me!
Kill this form if you must! You will only free me, Darkin! And I will find you and slay you, Varus!
Legends do not slay the dragon, Tryndamere. Legends learn to run.
Let me tear their flesh from them!
Lunari, your light fails! What can you do to me?
Make your death worthy of my time!
Mortal habit, the breathing. Bastard habit! The suffering!
Now, at last I have found you, demon sorceress! What trickery is this?! (to Syndra)
Now, friend, we have saved the apocalypse! Let us go our separate ways!
Now, Pantheon. We shall fight forever!
Now, Pantheon. We are doomed to struggle forever.
Ooh, a challenge. I love challenges! Oh, you meant this runt? What a waste of my time.
Ornn, my brother! We are destined to fight!
Pantheon! The man's unbroken will, twisting a Darkin! Now you die!
Poor Tryndamere. Your minuscule brain cannot fathom the depth of your failure!
See? See what you made me do!
The heavens are not done with me. I am not done with them!
The world denied my greatness! Now, I destroy it!
There are three certainties in life: honor, death and hangovers!
They think me defeated? How amusing.
They will call me villain. Come, let me earn their hatred!
This form is but a shadow of my true power!
Three, four… It matters not! I will slay them all!
Tides of blood! Pain that never ends! Let them break against me!
Tryndamere, you will suffer! You will suffer!
Tryndamere, your death will be the grand finale of this little ditty.
Tryndamere! Let us consume each other!
We are going to destroy the universe, Jarvan IV. It is just science.
What weapons are you supposed to be throwing at me, Leona? Sunlight?
Why do we feel nothing? Why do I feel nothing?
Why, Kayn? Why have you become such nonsense?
World Ender? Do they think that name supposed to frighten me?
World Ender? Ha! I will show you an end!
You know me too well, Pantheon.
You wretched, vile creature! I am Darkin, I will kill you all!
Akali's no problem once you know her weak spots.
Am I to play the role of mouse to some crow?
Any true beauty is an exception.
Be careful in the world of men
Careful now. Don't get blood on the tails.

voice_line: I don't hide my nature. I revel in it.

voice_line: Love is a game I always win.

People have said I'm charming. Or maybe they said

If you don't know who I am

Time to show them what fury looks like!
Victory is just a headbutt away.
I guess I’ll go cry now.
I just want someone to hug me.
It’s okay... I’m used to it...
Sometimes I think I’m the reason it rains.

voice_line: I am the storm given form.
My wings carry the hopes of many.
The chill will freeze their blood.
We are all connected through the snow.
You will be reborn in frost.
Freljord is my home and duty.
Keep your eyes on the enemy.
Let’s see how strong they are.
They will know the strength of the north.
War is no reason to stop diplomacy.
We take only what is ours.
My brilliance will be their undoing.
Let me remind them who I am.
They look up and see only stars. I see conquest.
Their gravity is nothing to mine.
I gave them magic. I can take it back.
You dare reach for the stars?
You exist because I allow it.
Bend the knee or break beneath it.

I will reclaim what was lost.
Let them feel the wrath of the desert.
I am the Emperor of the Sands.
The sun never sets on Shurima.
I walk the path of kings.
Their bones will pave my kingdom.
The age of men is over; Shurima shall rise.
Fired up and ready to serve.
This world will turn to ash.
Watch it all go up in flames.
Always bring a shield to a fistfight!
An ally in need? I am on the way!
Even the heaviest door can be opened.
Let us go—this will be fun!

if I do say so myself.

One strike is all I need.

One glance is all it takes.

Keep up or be left behind.

By the light of the moon.

It is not strength without purpose.
The truth is revealed through struggle.
